title: French protests reach climax ahead of ruling on Macron's pension reform plan
description: It was almost a last chance to get their voices heard ahead of a critical ruling on France's pension reforms.

title: Sunak condemns Indian High Commission violence as Modi says act against 'anti-India elements'
description: The prime minister has condemned recent violence at the Indian High Commission in London during a phone call with his counterpart Narendra Modi.

title: Shock as 'world class' rally driver, 33, killed in crash
description: Irish rally driver Craig Breen has died aged 33 after a crash in Croatia.

title: Ghana becomes first country to approve Oxford malaria vaccine
description: Ghana has become the first country in the world to approve a new malaria vaccine developed by Oxford University.

title: Cannes Film Festival nominees announced with record number of female directors on shortlist
description: New films from Wes Anderson and Ken Loach will be among those battling it out at the Cannes Film Festival when it kicks off next month, with a record number of female directors making the shortlist.

title: Protesters storm Louis Vuitton HQ in Paris ahead of decision on pension reforms
description: Protesters have stormed the headquarters of luxury fashion label Louis Vuitton on the eve of an expected ruling on controversial pension reforms in France.

title: Putin critic Navalny possibly 'being poisoned' in prison, spokesperson suggests
description: Alexei Navalny, the jailed critic of Vladimir Putin, is grappling with a mystery ailment in prison that could be the result of a slow-acting poison, his spokesperson has suggested.

title: Secret Pentagon documents leak suspect 'is gun enthusiast who ran gaming chatroom'
description: The man behind a hugely embarrassing leak of highly classified military documents is believed to be a young gun enthusiast who shared the secrets in a group for gamers.

title: North Korea missile launch sparks panic and evacuations in Japan
description: A missile launched by North Korea caused alarm and panic in Japan before the weapon fell into the sea.

title: Hippo descended from Pablo Escobar's herd dies after being hit by a car
description: A hippo descended from those owned by the Colombian cocaine kingpin Pablo Escobar has died after being struck by an SUV.
